A  former governor of Osun State ,Prince Olagunsoye Oyinlola  has described the death of Senator Abiola Ajimobi as a great loss to Nigeria and Yorubaland in particular. He noted that Ajimobi had a very large heart in his dealings with all manner of persons who came his way while his politics was clearly without bitterness. Oyinlola added that the late ex-governor gave a good account of himself first as senator, then as governor, leaving behind legacy programmes and projects that will forever mark him out as a very successful politician. He prayed for the repose of his soul and for his family to have the fortitude to bear the loss. 